headline: COST Q3 Deep Dive: Member Engagement and New Store Openings Shape Results
summary: Membership-only discount retailer Costco (NASDAQ:COST) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 8.1% year on year to $86.16 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $5.87 per share was 1.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: COST and KMX- Two Consumer Stocks on Divergent Paths
summary: Costco Wholesale Corp. (COST) just reported earnings per share and revenue above estimates. But CarMax Inc. (KMX) shares just plunged the most in the S&P 500 Index (^SPX) after the in-person used car seller reported angsty consumers held back from buying cars in the past quarter, mentions Tom Bruni, editor-in-chief of The Daily Rip by Stocktwits.
